# Git & deploy rules

## Branches
- `main` = production (auto-deploys to https://hamsaplou.com)
- `staging` = staging (auto-deploys to https://staging--hsl1.netlify.app)
- Feature branches: `feat/<short-name>` or `fix/<short-name>` (merge into `staging`)

## Flow
```
# work on staging (or feature → staging)
git checkout staging
git pull --rebase
# … edit …
git add -A
git commit -m "<type>: <imperative summary>"
# preflight: run scripts/preflight.ps1
git push origin staging
# wait for Netlify staging deploy to go green; test on staging URL
# only then promote:
git checkout main
git pull --rebase
git merge --no-ff staging
git push origin main
```

## Never
- `git push --force` / `--force-with-lease` (without explicit human "go")
- Push direct to `main` from a feature branch (always via `staging`)
- Commit `.env`, service role keys, JWTs, or password-protected files
- Skip `git pull --rebase` before push (causes divergence)

## Always
- Run `scripts/preflight.ps1` before `git push`
- Stop Vite dev server before git ops (file locks)
- If you hit stale `.git/index.lock` or `.git/config.lock`: confirm no process holds it, then delete
- Watch for the nested `D:\hsl\HSL` folder — it's gitignored; if git ever shows it tracked, run `git rm --cached HSL`

## Commit message format
```
<type>: <imperative summary under 60 chars>

[optional body explaining why]
```
Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `chore`, `db`, `style`, `test`.

## Netlify
- `VITE_*` env vars are inlined at build time → changing one requires a new deploy
- Verify deploy state = `ready` via `mcp__netlify__get-project` before declaring "shipped"
- Never delete env vars without confirming with the human
